    "One recent work, probably the first to build on the success of ChatGPT, used the autoregressive model to create a tool called DrugGPT for ligand creation, emphasizing protein-ligand discovery and chemical space exploration (Li et al., 2023).",
    "To find new compounds that can associate with specific proteins, researchers in this work used the DrugGPT model to learn from a large quantity of protein-ligand binding data.",
    "The GPT-2 model was trained and optimized to meet the needs of the pharmaceutical industry.",
    "To accommodate the unique properties of proteins and ligands, they discarded the original tokenizer in favor of a BPEbased redesign and started training the GPT-2 model from scratch.",
    "DrugGPT can better record and comprehend drug compounds' chemical rules and structural details with this update."
